rComments: Approachable and fair. Gives good direction.

He is a professional lecturing on the field he teaches - so provides real world input and connections in his classes. This is a 3rd year course so you should have some background knowledge in geographyplanning. But he is always available during his posted hours or by email for help.

This professor seems interesting and nice, though bitter at first.  When I tried to ask for help from him, he was extremely unhelpful and seemed to expect me to know everything. If you're in Urban Geography and you take this course, you'll do fine. If you're not, beware.  He's not the type to point you in any directions.
Not a good professor. He is adjunct so its just an extra thing for him. Cannot teach. I learnt very little from his lectures, the textbook was my only source.

Quite a pompous prof who gives the impression he is 'better' than his students. He constantly criticizes the ideas of his students, yet fails to guide them. Be aware that if you take his class you will regret it.
Quite possibly the worst prof. at U of T. Very arrogant and pretentious. Expects you to be experts like himself.  Do not take this class.
This teacher clearly has some sort of bitterness towards the world. Unfortunately, this bitterness transfers into his teaching. AVOID THIS PROF.
